==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fathom
<hw>Fath"om</hw> <pr>(f⟦acr⟧⟦th⟧"⟦ucr⟧m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>fadme</ets>, <ets>fa⟦edh⟧me</ets>, AS. <ets>f⟦ae⟧⟦edh⟧m</ets>
fathom, the embracing arms; akin to OS. <ets>fa⟦edh⟧mos</ets> the
outstretched arms, D. <ets>vadem</ets>, <ets>vaam</ets>, fathom, OHG.
<ets>fadom</ets>, <ets>fadum</ets>, G. <ets>faden</ets> fathom, thread,
Icel. <ets>fa⟦edh⟧mr</ets> fathom, Sw. <ets>famn</ets>, Dan.
<ets>favn</ets>; cf. Gr. <?/<?/<?/<?/<?/<?/<?/<?/<?/<?/ to spread out,
<?/<?/<?/<?/<?/<?/<?/ outspread, flat, L. <ets>patere</ets> to lie open,
extend. Cf. <er>Patent</er>, <er>Petal</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
measure of length, containing six feet; the space to which a man can
extend his arms; -- used chiefly in measuring cables, cordage, and the
depth of navigable water by soundings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The measure or extant of one's capacity; depth, as
of intellect; profundity; reach; penetration.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Another of his <qex>fathom</qex> they have none⟦br⟧
To lead their business.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fathom</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Fathom
<hw>Fath"om</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Fathomed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Fathoming</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To encompass with
the arms extended or encircling; to measure by throwing the arms about;
to span.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Purchas.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To measure by a sounding line; especially, to sound
the depth of; to penetrate, measure, and comprehend; to get to the
bottom of.</def> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The page of life that was spread out before me seemed dull and
commonplace, only because I had not <qex>fathomed</qex> its deeper
import.</q> <rj><qau>Hawthotne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fathomable</ent>⟦br⟧
